we are given a binary tree and p and q nodes . our job is to find lowest common ancestor between them.
Algoritm:
1. If root is null, return null.

2. If root is p or q, return root.

3. Search for p and q in the left subtree.

4. Search for p and q in the right subtree.

5. If left and right both return non-null:
   - One node was found on the left side.
   - One node was found on the right side.
   - So current root is the LCA.

6. If only left is non-null, return left.

7. If only right is non-null, return right.

8. If both are null, return null.

Code:
class Solution {
    public TreeNode lowestCommonAncestor(TreeNode root, TreeNode p, TreeNode q) {

        // If root is null, there is nothing to find
        if (root == null) return null;

        // If root is p or q, return root
        if (root == p || root == q) return root;

        // Search left subtree
        TreeNode left = lowestCommonAncestor(root.left, p, q);

        // Search right subtree
        TreeNode right = lowestCommonAncestor(root.right, p, q);

        // If both sides found something, root is the LCA
        if (left != null && right != null) return root;

        // Otherwise return whichever side found p or q
        return left != null ? left : right;
    }
}
